Standards-Version: 3.9.6

Package: qbone
Architecture: armhf
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, iproute2, ifupdown, bridge-utils
Description: PDP-11 Qbus device emulator for the QBone cape
 Emulates Qbus mass storage, serial and Ethernet controllers for a physical
 PDP-11, on a BeagleBone Black carrying a QBone cape. The PRU firmware that
 drives the bus is built into the executable, and a web interface on port 80
 operates the machine: device parameters, disk images, console streams and a
 live dashboard.
 .
 The cape's device tree overlay and the PRU interface are boot-time settings.
 Run qbone-setup after installing: it applies them, checks the hardware, puts
 the emulated Ethernet controller on the network and starts the services. See
 /usr/share/doc/qbone/README.Debian.
